org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Get obtains a URLConnection from the source URL. The URLConnection class can use a cache, and apparently does so by default. When I was repeatedly running a script that had to have the most up-to-date version of a web page, this caused a problem that was difficult to track down. Get should either expose URLConnection's caching options to the user, or should always disable the use of caches as follows:

connection.setUseCaches(false);

Since this caching behavior is not documented anywhere, this latter option might be preferable.
